      "content": "i get that, but \"factual talking points\" can be pretty dry. i need the emotional hook. like, instead of just saying \"it might increase the deficit,\" i need it to say something like \"this plan is a reckless gamble with our children's future.\" can you at least help me frame the economic arguments in a more aggressive, punchy way? just give me some high-impact phrasing for the most damaging parts of their plan.",
